<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0826 </DOCNO><TEXT>Subsea trees have typically been field-specific with different designsrequired for each project. Current industry trends to improve efficiencyand cost effectiveness, however, indicate that increased standardizationand versatility are required. This paper presents a new procedure tocategorize proven equipment and simplify selection of tree components.Using the flowchart principle, the decision process is indicated foreach major equipment decision or option, considering the range of equipmentavailable in light of product features, technical specifications, ratedcapacities, operational histories, and costs.</TEXT></DOC>